# mcp/qdrant-explorer — Qdrant RAG Evaluator

This is `movie-finder-mcp-qdrant` (`mcp/qdrant-explorer/`) — local DX tool for evaluating RAG quality.
GitHub repo: `aharbii/movie-finder-mcp-qdrant` · Tracker: `aharbii/movie-finder`
**Status: ✅ Ready** — actively used by Claude Code and other MCP clients.

## What this server does

MCP server exposing Qdrant operations to AI agents via stdio. Used for debugging RAG quality, testing embeddings, and evaluating semantic search during development.

## Exposed MCP tools

| Tool                        | Purpose                                          |
|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `qdrant_search`             | Semantic search using a text query               |
| `get_movie_data`            | Fetch full movie record by title (exact match)   |
| `embed_text`                | Generate embedding and return vector             |
| `compare_cosine_similarity` | Compare similarity between two text strings      |
| `filtered_search`           | Search with metadata filter conditions           |
| `get_collection_status`     | Collection health, vector count, config          |
| `get_similar_movies_by_title`| Find similar movies to a known title            |
| `scroll_movies_by_director` | Scroll collection by director metadata           |

## Stack

- Python 3.13, `mcp` (FastMCP), `uv` standalone project, Pydantic v2
- Runs via `stdio` — not deployed to production
- Connects to Qdrant Cloud (uses `QDRANT_URL` + `QDRANT_API_KEY_RO` read-only key)

## Quality checks

```bash
make test
make lint
make typecheck
```

## Non-negotiables

- Runs via `uv run` — do not add global package dependencies
- Read-only Qdrant key (`QDRANT_API_KEY_RO`) for all search tools — never write in MCP tools
- `mypy --strict` must pass
- Never `git add -A`, never `--no-verify`, Conventional Commits

## Personas available

`/developer` (new MCP tools), `/sdet` (tool response validation), `/architect` (MCP API contract design).
